text: Lynne Janice Kosky (2 September 1958 - 4 December 2014) was a former Australian politician and senior minister in the Parliament of Victoria. She represented the electoral district of Altona in the Victorian Legislative Assembly for the Australian Labor Party from 1996 to 2010 Kosky died from breast cancer in Melbourne, Victoria, Australia, aged 56. ==References== ==Other websites== *Kosky, Lynne Janice , Re-member Parliamentary Profile Category:1958 births Category:2014 deaths Category:Deaths from breast cancer Category:Politicians from Melbourne
